# Shader and Rendering Workflow

- For non-trivial shader/rendering changes, include debug visualization hooks or inspection toggles.
- Document known artifacts and fallback behavior for non-critical effects.
- Validate performance impact for representative scenes before considering the change complete.
- Keep rendering code downstream from simulation and topology truth; do not encode gameplay authority in visual logic.
